Singh next starred opposite [[Deepika Padukone]] in [[Sanjay Leela Bhansali]]'s adaptation of [[William Shakespeare]]'s ''[[Romeo and Juliet]]'', entitled ''[[Goliyon Ki Raasleela Ram-Leela]]'', in which he played Ram, a [[Gujarati people|Gujarati boy]] based on the character of [[Romeo]].<ref>{{cite news|title=First look Ram Leela: Meet Romeo Ranveer and Juliet Deepika |url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/first-poster-of-ram-leela-ranveer-singh-deepika-padukone/1/247370.html |work=India Today |accessdate=16 July 2013 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6JwCOFmHR?url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/first-poster-of-ram-leela-ranveer-singh-deepika-padukone/1/247370.html |archivedate=27 September 2013 |url-status=dead |df= }}</ref> Bhansali was impressed by Singh's performance in ''Band Baaja Baaraat'' and decided to cast him for the film.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://zeenews.india.com/entertainment/bollywood/ranveer-singh-to-romance-kareena-in-ram-leela_112369.html |title=Ranveer Singh to romance Kareena in 'Ram Leela' |date=30 May 2012 |accessdate=24 August 2012 |publisher=Zee News |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131017184332/http://zeenews.india.com/entertainment/bollywood/ranveer-singh-to-romance-kareena-in-ram-leela_112369.html |archivedate=17 October 2013 |df= }}</ref> ''Goliyon Ki Raasleela Ram-Leela'' generated positive reviews from critics, as did Singh's performance.<ref name="ht2013-11-15">{{cite news |last=Uniyal |first=Parmita |title=Movie review: Bhansali's Ram-leela is his best ever, say critics |url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/entertainment/bollywood/movie-review-bhansali-s-ram-leela-is-his-best-ever-say-critics/article1-1151490.aspx |accessdate=15 November 2013 |newspaper=Hindustan Times |date=15 November 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131115083944/http://www.hindustantimes.com/entertainment/bollywood/movie-review-bhansali-s-ram-leela-is-his-best-ever-say-critics/article1-1151490.aspx |archivedate=15 November 2013 |df= }}</ref> Writing for ''[[India Today]]'', Rohit Khilnani commented that "Singh has everything going for him here. His Bollywood hero entry scene lying down on a bike in the song 'Tattad Tattad' is outstanding. He learnt a new language to better his performance for the character Ram and it paid off. In his fourth film he has the presence of a star."<ref>{{cite news|last=Khilnani |first=Rohit |title=Movie Review: Ram Leela is a spectacular show! |url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/movie-review-ram-leela/1/324858.html |accessdate=15 November 2013 |work=India Today |date=15 November 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131115081937/http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/movie-review-ram-leela/1/324858.html |archivedate=15 November 2013 |df= }}</ref> The film emerged as Singh's biggest commercial success,<ref>{{cite web|title=Goliyon Ki Raasleela Ram-Leela' earns Rs 93.58 crores in opening weekend |url=http://www.deccanchronicle.com/131120/entertainment-bollywood/article/goliyon-ki-raasleela-ram-leela-earns-rs-9358-crores-opening |date=16 November 2013 |work=Deccan Chronicle |accessdate=22 November 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131123060809/http://www.deccanchronicle.com/131120/entertainment-bollywood/article/goliyon-ki-raasleela-ram-leela-earns-rs-9358-crores-opening |archivedate=23 November 2013 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.koimoi.com/box-office/ramleela-grosses-100-crore-worldwide-at-the-box-office/ |title=Ramleela Grosses 100 Crore Worldwide At The Box Office |publisher=Koimoi.com |accessdate=18 December 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131203020135/http://www.koimoi.com/box-office/ramleela-grosses-100-crore-worldwide-at-the-box-office/ |archivedate= 3 December 2013 |df= |date=20 November 2013 }}</ref> with worldwide revenues of {{INRConvert|2.02|b}}.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.boxofficeindia.com/boxnewsdetail.php?page=shownews&articleid=6306&nCat= |title=Goliyon Ki Raasleela Ram - Leela Set For 200 Crore Worldwide |publisher=Box Office India |date=9 December 2013 |accessdate=18 December 2013|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131215160117/http://www.boxofficeindia.com/boxnewsdetail.php?page=shownews&articleid=6306&nCat=|archivedate=15 December 2013|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.koimoi.com/box-office/ramleela-all-set-to-join-koimois-top-worldwide-grossing-movies-list/ |title=Ramleela All Set To Join Koimoi's 'Top Worldwide Grossing Movies' List |publisher=Koimoi.com |date=11 December 2013 |accessdate=18 December 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131218105403/http://www.koimoi.com/box-office/ramleela-all-set-to-join-koimois-top-worldwide-grossing-movies-list/ |archivedate=18 December 2013 |df= }}</ref> For his portrayal, he received several recognitions, including a [[Filmfare Award for Best Actor|Best Actor]] nomination at Filmfare.<ref name="59filmfare">{{cite news|title=59th Idea Filmfare Awards Nominations |url=http://www.filmfare.com/news/59th-idea-filmfare-awards-nominations-5138.html |accessdate=14 January 2014 |work=Filmfare |date=13 January 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140115044052/http://www.filmfare.com/news/59th-idea-filmfare-awards-nominations-5138.html |archivedate=15 January 2014 |df= }}</ref>

In 2014, Singh starred as a Bengali criminal in [[Ali Abbas Zafar]]'s ''[[Gunday]]'', alongside [[Arjun Kapoor]], [[Priyanka Chopra]] and [[Irrfan Khan]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-08-24/news-interviews/33365530_1_arjun-kapoor-ali-zafar-ranveer-singh|title=Ali Abbas and Yash Raj team up again|last=Misra|first=Iti Shree|date=24 August 2012|accessdate=2 January 2014|work=The Times of India|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131215024623/http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-08-24/news-interviews/33365530_1_arjun-kapoor-ali-zafar-ranveer-singh|archive-date=15 December 2013|url-status=live}}
</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.yashrajfilms.com/movies/MovieIndividual.aspx?MovieID=b1bae9c1-ca58-477e-b9fb-81d1e0fce6cc |title=Gunday |accessdate=2 January 2014 |publisher=Yash Raj Films |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131222091910/http://www.yashrajfilms.com/Movies/MovieIndividual.aspx?MovieID=b1bae9c1-ca58-477e-b9fb-81d1e0fce6cc |archivedate=22 December 2013 |df= }}</ref> David Chute of ''[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]'' praised Singh's screen presence and wrote that he "tucks the movie's center of interest under his arm and takes it with him — even though he has the could-be-thankless "good brother" role".<ref>{{cite news|last=Chute |first=David |url=https://variety.com/2014/film/reviews/film-review-gunday-1201103256/ |title=Gunday Review- An Entertaining Buddy-Gangster Melodrama |work=Variety |accessdate=30 December 2014 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141224124044/http://variety.com/2014/film/reviews/film-review-gunday-1201103256/ |archivedate=24 December 2014 |df= }}</ref> Also, Singh's chemistry with Kapoor was considered by critic Rohit Khilnani to the prime asset of the film.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/gunday-review-starring-priyanka-chopra-ranveer-singh-arjun-kapoor/1/343438.html |title=Movie review: Gunday is old wine in a new bottle, it tastes awesome! |author=Khilnani, Rohit |work=India Today |date=14 February 2014 |accessdate=25 February 2014 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140224223702/http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/gunday-review-starring-priyanka-chopra-ranveer-singh-arjun-kapoor/1/343438.html |archivedate=24 February 2014 |df= }}</ref> ''Gunday'' proved to be Singh's biggest box office opener,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.boxofficeindia.com/Details/art_detail/gundayfirstdaycollectionsreport |title=Boxoffice: Gunday First Day Collections |publisher=Box Office India |accessdate=15 February 2014 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140223120701/http://www.boxofficeindia.com/Details/art_detail/gundayfirstdaycollectionsreport |archivedate=23 February 2014 |df= }}</ref> and eventually emerged a box-office success with a revenue of {{INRConvert|1|b|}} worldwide.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/articles/540092/20140223/gunday-box-office-collection-100-crore-ranveer.htm |title='Gunday' Box Office Collection: Ranveer-Arjun Starrer Grosses 100 Crore Worldwide |author=Seshagiri, Sangeetha |work=International Business Times |date=23 February 2014 |accessdate=25 February 2014 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140223153527/http://www.ibtimes.co.in/articles/540092/20140223/gunday-box-office-collection-100-crore-ranveer.htm |archivedate=23 February 2014 |df= }}</ref> After a cameo appearance in ''[[Finding Fanny]]'', Singh starred as a gangster in [[Shaad Ali]]'s unsuccessful crime drama ''[[Kill Dil]]'' opposite Parineeti Chopra and [[Ali Zafar]] and received negative reviews.<ref>{{cite news|title=After Ramleela, Ranveer Singh and Deepika Padukone to share screen space in Finding Fanny Fernandes |url=http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/1901468/report-after-ramleela-ranveer-singh-and-deepika-padukone-to-share-screen-space-in-finding-fanny-fernandes |accessdate=20 October 2013 |newspaper=Daily News and Analysis |date=10 October 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131014000603/http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/1901468/report-after-ramleela-ranveer-singh-and-deepika-padukone-to-share-screen-space-in-finding-fanny-fernandes |archivedate=14 October 2013 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title='Kill Dil' gets 'kill'ed officially; collects a mere Rs 20 crore in opening weekend |url=http://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/kill-dil-gets-killed-officially-collects-a-mere-rs-13-crore-in-opening-weekend/#sthash.OigToazn.dpuf |accessdate=20 December 2014 |newspaper=The Indian Express |date=17 November 2014 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141220142823/http://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/kill-dil-gets-killed-officially-collects-a-mere-rs-13-crore-in-opening-weekend/ |archivedate=20 December 2014 |df= }}</ref>

===Established actor (2015–present)===
[[File:Ranveer at filmfare (cropped).jpg|thumb|upright|left|Singh at the [[61st Filmfare Awards]] ceremony, where he won the [[Filmfare Award for Best Actor|Best Actor]] award for portraying [[Bajirao I]] in ''[[Bajirao Mastani]]'' (2015)]]
In [[Zoya Akhtar]]'s ensemble comedy-drama ''[[Dil Dhadakne Do]]'' (2015), Singh starred with [[Anil Kapoor]], [[Shefali Shah]] and Priyanka Chopra as the younger sibling of a dysfunctional Punjabi business family who aspires to become a pilot. Writing for ''[[Mumbai Mirror]]'', Kunal Guha found Singh to be the "surprise element" of the film; he praised his "immaculate comic timing" and took note of his subtlety.<ref>{{cite news|last=Guha |first=Kunal |title=Film Review: Dil Dhadakne Do |url=http://www.mumbaimirror.com/entertainment/bollywood/Film-review-Dil-Dhadakne-Do/articleshow/47547376.cms |work=[[Mumbai Mirror]] |date=5 June 2015 |accessdate=5 June 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150606131650/http://www.mumbaimirror.com/entertainment/bollywood/Film-review-Dil-Dhadakne-Do/articleshow/47547376.cms |archivedate= 6 June 2015 |df= }}</ref> Commercially, the film underperformed.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://boxofficeindia.com/movie.php?movieid=2879 |title=Dil Dhadakne Do |publisher=Box Office India |accessdate=14 February 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190214233318/https://boxofficeindia.com/movie.php?movieid=2879 |archive-date=14 February 2019 |url-status=live  }}</ref> He next reunited with Sanjay Leela Bhansali in the period romance ''[[Bajirao Mastani]]'' (2015), opposite Deepika Padukone and Priyanka Chopra. He portrayed [[Bajirao I]], for which he shaved his head and to prepare, he locked himself in a hotel room for 21 days.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/Exclusive-Ranveer-Singh-shaves-his-head-for-Bajirao-Mastani/articleshow/44887453.cms |title=Exclusive: Ranveer Singh shaves his head for Bajirao Mastani |last=Gupta |first=Priya |work=The Times of India |date=21 October 2014 |accessdate=19 December 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150216022938/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/Exclusive-Ranveer-Singh-shaves-his-head-for-Bajirao-Mastani/articleshow/44887453.cms |archivedate=16 February 2015 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=When Ranveer Singh locked himself up in a hotel room for 21 days |url=http://www.mid-day.com/articles/when-ranveer-singh-locked-himself-up-in-a-hotel-room-for-21-days/16770197 |work=Mid Day |date=14 December 2015 |accessdate=19 December 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151216203114/http://www.mid-day.com/articles/when-ranveer-singh-locked-himself-up-in-a-hotel-room-for-21-days/16770197 |archivedate=16 December 2015 |df= }}</ref> [[Raja Sen]] wrote that Singh "brings his character to life and does so with both machismo and grace", and commended him for his perfecting his character's gait and accent.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/review/review-priyanka-ranveer-are-terrific-in-bajirao-mastani/20151218.htm |title=Review: Priyanka, Ranveer are terrific in Bajirao Mastani |last=Sen |first=Raja |publisher=Rediff.com |date=18 December 2015 |accessdate=19 December 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151220070433/http://www.rediff.com/movies/review/review-priyanka-ranveer-are-terrific-in-bajirao-mastani/20151218.htm |archivedate=20 December 2015 |df= }}</ref> The film earned {{INRConvert|3.5|b}} to become one of the [[List of highest-grossing Indian films|highest-grossing Indian films]], and garnered Singh the [[Filmfare Award for Best Actor]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://boxofficeindia.com/art_detail.php?articalid=1734 |title=Worldwide 2015 – Dilwale Nearing Prem Ratan Dhan Payo |date=14 January 2016 |publisher=Box Office India |accessdate=24 January 2016 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160117060809/http://boxofficeindia.com/art_detail.php?articalid=1734 |archivedate=17 January 2016 |url-status=dead |df= }}</ref><ref name="win">{{cite news|url=http://www.filmfare.com/news/full-list-of-winners-of-the-61st-britannia-filmfare-awards-11841.html |title=Full list of winners of the 61st Britannia Filmfare Awards |work=Filmfare |date=15 January 2016 |accessdate=16 January 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160316165017/http://www.filmfare.com/news/full-list-of-winners-of-the-61st-britannia-filmfare-awards-11841.html |archivedate=16 March 2016 |df= }}</ref>

In 2016, Singh starred in Aditya Chopra's comedy-romance ''[[Befikre]]'' opposite [[Vaani Kapoor]]. He played Dharam Gulati, a stand-up comic whose romantic liaisons with Kapoor's character leads to conflict between them. Set in Paris, ''Befikre'' marked the fourth project to be directed by Chopra.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/befikre-review-round-heres-what-critics-have-say-about-ranveer-singh-vaani-kapoors-parisian-707617 |title=Befikre review round-up: Critics have given their verdict on Ranveer Singh and Vaani Kapoor's film |last=Sarkar |first=Prarthna |publisher=International Business Times |date=9 December 2016 |accessdate=10 December 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161210131156/http://www.ibtimes.co.in/befikre-review-round-heres-what-critics-have-say-about-ranveer-singh-vaani-kapoors-parisian-707617 |archivedate=10 December 2016 |df= }}</ref> Singh performed a nude scene for it, a rare occurrence in an Indian film.<ref>{{cite news|last=Mehta|first=Sushant|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/movies/gossip/story/ranveer-singh-butt-naked-vaani-kapoor-befikre-interview-346592-2016-10-14|title=Exclusive: Ranveer Singh has gone butt naked for Befikre. For real!|work=India Today|date=14 October 2016|access-date=24 January 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180125022316/https://www.indiatoday.in/movies/gossip/story/ranveer-singh-butt-naked-vaani-kapoor-befikre-interview-346592-2016-10-14|archivedate=25 January 2018}}</ref> Jay Weissberg of ''[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]'' found the film to be an "overly energetic twist on the old friends with benefits theme" and criticised Singh's "manic behavior".<ref>{{cite news|last=Weissberg|first=Jay|url=https://variety.com/2017/film/reviews/befikre-film-review-1201950595/|title=Film Review: 'Befikre'|date=3 January 2017|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|access-date=3 January 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170104050548/http://variety.com/2017/film/reviews/befikre-film-review-1201950595/|archivedate=4 January 2017}}</ref> It underperformed at the box office.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://boxofficeindia.com/movie.php?movieid=3437|title=Befikre|publisher=Box Office India|access-date=24 January 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171008200322/https://boxofficeindia.com/movie.php?movieid=3437|archivedate=8 October 2017}}</ref>

After a year-long absence from the screen, Singh portrayed [[Alauddin Khalji|Alauddin Khilji]], a ruthless Muslim king, in Sanjay Leela Bhansali's period drama ''[[Padmaavat]]'' (2018), co-starring Deepika Padukone and [[Shahid Kapoor]], which marked his third collaboration with Bhansali and Padukone.<ref name="padmavati">{{cite news|title=Team Padmavati starts shooting today |url=http://www.filmfare.com/news/team-padmavati-starts-shooting-today-16399.html |accessdate=1 November 2016 |work=Filmfare |date=1 November 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161101164843/http://www.filmfare.com/news/team-padmavati-starts-shooting-today-16399.html |archivedate= 1 November 2016 |df= }}</ref> [[Saffron terror|Right-wing Hindu groups]]&nbsp;speculated that the film distorted historical facts, and issued violent threats against the cast and crew. The film's release was deferred and was allowed for exhibition after several modifications were made to it.<ref>{{cite news |last=Ray |first=Saptarshi |title=Bounty placed on Bollywood actress' head after Hindu-Muslim film outrage |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2017/11/17/bounty-placed-bollywood-actress-head-hindu-muslim-film-outrage/ |work=[[The Daily Telegraph]] |date=17 November 2017 |accessdate=2 December 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171118052745/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2017/11/17/bounty-placed-bollywood-actress-head-hindu-muslim-film-outrage/ |archivedate=18 November 2017  }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ndtv.com/india-news/film-padmavati-to-get-ua-certificate-title-may-be-changed-to-padmavat-1793855|title=Censor Board Wants "Padmavati" Renamed "Padmavat", 5 Changes To Film|publisher=NDTV|date=30 December 2017|accessdate=30 December 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171230133652/https://www.ndtv.com/india-news/film-padmavati-to-get-ua-certificate-title-may-be-changed-to-padmavat-1793855|archivedate=30 December 2017}}</ref> Ankur Pathak of ''[[HuffPost]]'' criticised the film's misogynistic and regressive themes, but praised Singh for his "astute brilliance" in depicting Khilji's bisexuality.<ref>{{cite news|last=Pathak|first=Ankur|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.in/2018/01/23/padmaavat-review-ranveer-singhs-queer-act-shatters-the-glass-ceiling-in-indian-film-writing_a_23341645/|title='Padmaavat' Review: Ranveer Singh's Queer Act Shatters The Glass Ceiling In Indian Film Writing|date=24 January 2018|work=[[HuffPost]]|access-date=24 January 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180124061209/http://www.huffingtonpost.in/2018/01/23/padmaavat-review-ranveer-singhs-queer-act-shatters-the-glass-ceiling-in-indian-film-writing_a_23341645/|archivedate=24 January 2018}}</ref> Rajeev Masand opined that he "plays the part with the sort of grotesque flamboyance that makes it hard to look at anyone or anything else when he’s on the screen".<ref>{{cite web|last=Masand|first=Rajeev|url=http://www.news18.com/news/movies/padmaavat-movie-review-ranveer-singh-delicious-performance-is-its-biggest-strength-1639675.html|title=Padmaavat Movie Review: Ranveer Singh's Delicious Performance Is Its Biggest Strength|date=24 January 2018|publisher=News18|access-date=24 January 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180125020734/http://www.news18.com/news/movies/padmaavat-movie-review-ranveer-singh-delicious-performance-is-its-biggest-strength-1639675.html|archivedate=25 January 2018}}</ref> ''Padmaavat''{{'}}s production budget of {{INRConvert|2|b}} made it the [[List of most expensive Indian films#Hindi|most expensive Hindi film]] ever made at that time.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.boxofficeindia.com/report-details.php?articleid=3469|title=Padmavati Being Aimed For A February Release|publisher=Box Office India|date=8 December 2017|accessdate=8 December 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171208231459/http://www.boxofficeindia.com/report-details.php?articleid=3469|archivedate=8 December 2017}}</ref> With a worldwide gross of over {{INRConvert|5.7|b}}, it ranks as Singh's highest-grossing release and is among India cinema's biggest grossers.<ref name="2018w"/><ref>
{{cite web|url=https://boxofficeindia.com/report-details.php?articleid=3881|title=Worldwide Alltime : Padmaavat 7th - Baaghi 2 22nd|accessdate=26 April 2018|date=26 April 2018|publisher=Box Office India|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180426213042/https://boxofficeindia.com/report-details.php?articleid=3881|archive-date=26 April 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> He won the [[Filmfare Critics Award for Best Actor]] (shared with [[Ayushmann Khurrana]] for ''[[Andhadhun]]'') and gained a Best Actor nomination at the ceremony.<ref>{{cite news|title=Winners of the 64th Vimal Filmfare Awards 2019|url=https://www.filmfare.com/news/bollywood/all-winners-of-the-64th-vimal-filmfare-awards-2019_-33004-3.html|date=23 March 2019|accessdate=23 March 2019|work=[[Filmfare]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190323165124/https://www.filmfare.com/news/bollywood/all-winners-of-the-64th-vimal-filmfare-awards-2019_-33004-3.html|archive-date=23 March 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.filmfare.com/news/bollywood/nominations-for-the-64th-vimal-filmfare-awards-2019_-32898-1.html |title=Nominations for the 64th Vimal Filmfare Awards 2019 |work=Filmfare |date=12 March 2019 |access-date=13 March 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190316052927/https://www.filmfare.com/news/bollywood/nominations-for-the-64th-vimal-filmfare-awards-2019_-32898-1.html |archive-date=16 March 2019 |url-status=live  }}</ref>

